    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's really helpful, thanks. I see what you mean about the \"wide net.\" It just feels like they're trying to hide some ways to shift all the risk onto me. Is there anything else I should be looking for in the fine print to make sure they aren't being predatory or trying to sneak in extra liabilities?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are wise to be cautious; these contracts are often designed to favor the Client, which is always a risk when you're freelancing. Beyond the indemnification, watch out for clauses that dictate *how* you must handle these claims. Specifically, look for language that forces you to pay for their *own* internal investigation costs before the lawsuit even starts. Also, check the \"Limitation of Liability\" section—if it's missing or extremely one-sided, it means there's no cap on how much you could potentially owe them. Always try to negotiate a cap on your liability.",
      "source": "target",
